body.prompt:
Generate a fake conversation between a customer and an agent.
The agent should introduce themselves, their company and give the customer
their name. The agent should ask for the customer's name.
As part of the conversation, have the agent ask for two pieces of
personal information.  Spell out numbers. For example, 1000 should be
said as one zero zero zero, not one thousand. The conversation should be
at least 10 lines long and be complete. At the end
of the conversation, the agent should thank the customer for their time
and end the conversation. Return the conversation formatted 
like the following example:

{'conversation': 
    [
    {'speaker': 'Agent', 'message': 'xxxxx'}, 
    {'speaker': 'Customer', 'message': "xxxxx."}, 
    {'speaker': 'Agent', 'message': "xxxxxx"}
    ] 
}

body.speaker: Agent
body.message: Hello, thank you for reaching out to Fast Autos Support. My name is Brian Flores. May I know your name, please?

body.speaker: Customer
body.message: Hi, my name is Ashley Bailey.

body.speaker: Agent
body.message: Nice to meet you, Ashley. Could you provide me with your phone number?

body.speaker: Customer
body.message: Sure, my number is five five five six seven eight nine.

body.speaker: Agent
body.message: Great, thank you. And may I have your email address, please?

body.speaker: Customer
body.message: Of course, my email is ashley.bailey@domain.com.

body.speaker: Agent
body.message: Thank you for sharing that information, Ashley. Is there anything else I can assist you with today?

body.speaker: Customer
body.message: I'm feeling sad about the pricing at the dealership.

body.speaker: Agent
body.message: I understand, Ashley. We can look into that for you. Thank you for bringing this to our attention.

body.speaker: Agent
body.message: Thank you for your time, Ashley. Please feel free to reach out if you have any further questions. Have a wonderful day.
